					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/02/08/101158_how-to-increase-your-daily-writing.html#comments/3364&quot;&gt;nothing&lt;/a&gt;.

Set realistic writing goals. You are&#039;t going to go from writing 0 words a day to writing 5,000 words a day. Start with a realistic number (300 is a good number to begin with) and then add more when you are hitting the goal each day. Remember, there is no rule you need to stop once you reach your daily word count goal. So if your goal is 300 and you hit it and still have time, write more.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/02/08/101158_how-to-increase-your-daily-writing.html#comments/3364">nothing</a>.</p>
<p>Set realistic writing goals. You are&#8217;t going to go from writing 0 words a day to writing 5,000 words a day. Start with a realistic number (300 is a good number to begin with) and then add more when you are hitting the goal each day. Remember, there is no rule you need to stop once you reach your daily word count goal. So if your goal is 300 and you hit it and still have time, write more.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
